REMARK 280
REMARK 280 CRYSTALLIZATION CONDITIONS: COMMERCIAL SCREEN INDEX 44 (0.1 M
REMARK 280  HEPES PH 7.5, 25% W/V PEG3350) WAS CHOSEN FOR SARS-COV-2 NSP1
REMARK 280  (RESIDUES 10 TO 126) CRYSTALLISATION IN LARGE QUANTITIES USING
REMARK 280  HANGING DROP METHOD. FROZEN STOCKS OF SARS-COV-2 NSP1 (RESIDUES
REMARK 280  10 TO 126) WERE THAWED ON ICE AND CENTRIFUGED IN A THERMO
REMARK 280  SCIENTIFIC PICO 17 MICROCENTRIFUGE, 24-PL ROTOR AT 4 DEGREES,
REMARK 280  20000 RPM FOR 10 MIN TO REMOVE AGGREGATES BEFORE THE
REMARK 280  DETERMINATION OF THE PROTEIN CONCENTRATION. SUBSEQUENTLY, THE
REMARK 280  PROTEIN STOCK WAS DILUTED TO 20 MG/ML WITH PRECRYSTALLISATION
REMARK 280  BUFFER (10 MM HEPES AND 300 MM NACL). 400 UL OF INDEX CONDITION
REMARK 280  44 WAS ADDED INTO EACH RESERVOIR WELL. FIVE PROTEIN DROPS WERE
REMARK 280  SET ON EACH COVER SLIP BY MIXING 1 UL OF PROTEIN SOLUTION WITH 1
REMARK 280  UL OF THE RESERVOIR. THE 24-WELL LINBRO PLATES WERE INCUBATED AT
REMARK 280  18 DEGREES., VAPOR DIFFUSION, HANGING DROP, TEMPERATURE 291.15K
